<Sequential id="writing_survey_1" title="Writing Survey 1" launchable="true">
    <Vertical id="ws1_intro">
       <Markdown>
            # Writing Survey 1
            ## Introduction

            In this survey, you will reflect on how you feel about writing and various kinds
            of writing situations. To probe how you feel, you will be presented with a series of statements, and asked to indicate whether you (a) strongly agree, (b) agree, (c) disagree, or (d) strongly disagree with that statement. Work your way through these statements, picking the answer that seems to match your own experience and feelings best. There are quite a few statements to get through, so don't take too much time on any single statement. At the end, we will give you a computer-generated summary of your answers.
                        
       </Markdown>
    </Vertical>
    <SplitPanel id="ws1_Step_1" title="Survey Questions 1-5" sizes="80,20">
        <LeftPane>
            <Markdown>
                ## Questions 1-5
                Indicate how strongly you agree or disagree with the following statements.
            </Markdown>
            <TabularMCQ id="ws1_affect_1">
              cols: Strongly Agree, Agree, Disagree, Strongly Disagree
              rows: Writing is a skill I want to get better at.,It is frustrating to have to write about a subject that I did not choose.,Writing is usually boring for me.,I worry that other people will criticize my writing.,I like to write outside of school.
            </TabularMCQ>
            <Markdown id="ws1_directions">
              Select one option for each row. Your selections are automatically saved.
            </Markdown>
        </LeftPane>
        <RightPane>
           <ActionButton label="Compare my responses to a typical student's">
               <LLMAction target="ws1_response_summary_1">
                  BACKGROUND INFORMATION:
                   For the first survey page that asks about student feelings about writing,
                   Our column headers are: 
                         Strongly Agree (corresponding to 0),
                         Agree (corresponding to 1),
                         Disagree (corresponding to 2),
                         Strongly Disagree (corresponding to 3),

                   Our row headers are:
                   Writing is a skill I want to get better at.
                   It is frustrating to have to write about a subject that I did not choose.
                   Writing is usually boring for me.
                   I worry that other people will criticize my writing.
                   I like to write outside of school.                         
                   
                   Our data is: 
                   <Ref id="ws1_ref1" target="ws1_affect_1" />
                   
                  This data can be interpreted by mapping each number onto the column header it corresponds
                  to and using the row headers to indicate the frequency with which the student writes in each genre
                  for school.
                  
                  Typical students:
                         Agree (or strongly agree) that writing is a skill they want to get better at,
                         Agree that it is frustrating to have to write about a subject that they did not choose.
                         May agree or disagree about whether they consider writing usually boring,
                             but do not have strong feelings either way,
                         Disagree strongly with the statement that they worry about other people
                             criticizing their writing,
                         Disagree strongly with the statement that they like to write outside school.

                  DIRECTIONS: 
                   If any of the student's response data is blank, say so and stop; otherwise,
                   using the information from the data interpretation, and addressing the 
                   student as "you", write one sentence that explains how the student's feelings
                   resemble those of typical students, and (if appropriate) one sentence that
                   explains how the student's feelings are different from those of typical students. 
           </LLMAction>
           </ActionButton>
           <LLMFeedback id="ws1_response_summary_1" />
         </RightPane>
    </SplitPanel>
