                   I like it when I can focus and my writing flows.                    
                   
                   Our data is: 
                   <Ref id="ws1_ref6" target="ws1_affect_1" />
                   <Ref id="ws1_ref7" target="ws1_affect_2" />
                   <Ref id="ws1_ref8" target="ws1_affect_3" />
                   <Ref id="ws1_ref9" target="ws1_affect_4" />
                   <Ref id="ws1_ref10" target="ws1_affect_5" />
                   
                  This data can be interpreted by mapping each number onto the column header it corresponds
                  to and using the row headers to indicate the frequency with which the student writes in each genre
                  for school.
                  
                  These statements can be grouped into the following factors:
                  
                  Factor 1 (Difficulty/Interest). 
                  
                  Agreement with the following statements indicates the student feels that
                  writing is boring and difficult:
                  I dislike writing.
                  It is frustrating to write about a subject that I did not choose.
                  Writing is usually boring for me.
                  I find it difficult to communicate my ideas through writing.
                  I prefer to avoid writing when it isn't required.
                  Writing feels really hard.
                  
                  Disagreement with the following statements indicates the student feels
                  that writing is boring and difficult:
                  I find writing interesting.
                  I understand things better when I write about them.
                  
                  Factor 2 (Agency)
                  Agreement with the following statements indicates the student feels
                  a sense of control and agency in the writing process:
                  There are some subjects I really enjoy writing about.
                  I like it when I can focus and my writing flows.
                  There are some kinds of writing that I really like.
                  I enjoy writing most when I get to decide what to write about.
                  I like it when people compliment my writing skills.
                  It's important that I get a good grade on a writing assignment.
                  It upsets me when I get low grades on a writing assignment.
                
                  Factor 3 (Self-efficacy)
                  Agreement with the following statements indicates that the student
                  has a high degree of confidence in his/her writing skills:
                  I like getting lots of shares or likes on social media.
                  I get so involved in my writing that I often lose track of time.
                  I feel confident in my writing.
                  I usually enjoy writing in school.
                  When I write, I create content that I can be proud of.
                  I like to write outside of school.
                  
                  Disagreement with the following statement also suggests a high
                  degree of writing self-confidence:
                  I am too impatient to spend a lot of time writing.
                  
                  Factor 4 (Intrinsic value)
                  Agreement with the following statements indicates that the student believes
                  that writing has high intrinsic value as a skill he/she needs to learn:
                  Writing helps me learn.
                  I feel it is important to know how to write well.
                  Writing is a skill I want to get better at.
                  I worry that other people will criticize my writing.
 
                  DIRECTIONS: 
